title: Trinca Airport
text:
Trinca Airport is a public use <a href="airport">airport</a> in <a href="Sussex%20County%2C%20New%20Jersey">Sussex County, New Jersey</a>, United States. The airport is owned by <a href="Green%20Township%2C%20New%20Jersey">Green Township</a> and located three <a href="nautical%20mile">nautical mile</a>s (6 <a href="kilometre">km</a>) southwest of the <a href="central%20business%20district">central business district</a> of <a href="Andover%2C%20New%20Jersey">Andover</a>. Purchased by the municipality of <a href="Green%20Township%2C%20New%20Jersey">Green Township</a>, it will close September 30, 2020.
Facilities and aircraft.
Trinca Airport covers an area of 12 <a href="acre">acre</a>s (5 <a href="hectare">ha</a>) at an <a href="elevation">elevation</a> of 600 feet (183 m) above <a href="mean%20sea%20level">mean sea level</a>. It has one <a href="runway">runway</a> designated 6/24 with a <a href="grass">turf</a> surface measuring 1,924 by 135 feet (586 x 41 m).
For the 12-month period ending January 1, 2013, the airport had 11,395 <a href="general%20aviation">general aviation</a> aircraft operations, an average of 31 per day. At that time there were 10 aircraft based at this airport: 70% single-<a href="aircraft%20engine">engine</a>, 20% multi-engine, and 10% <a href="ultralight">ultralight</a>.
